other_tests.findings: The appendix is fluid filled, measuring up to 12 mm in maximum diameter with mild periappendiceal fat stranding.

Liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions; normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys; no free air, fluid or lymphadenopathy in the intra-abdominal cavity; appendix is fluid filled, concerning for appendicitis; no periappendiceal fluid or free gas noted.
